  "text": "Envoy v1.31.2 implements comprehensive HTTP request header injection validation through multiple layers of validation and sanitization mechanisms:\n\n## Header Validation Framework\n\nThe primary header validation implementation is located in `source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/`. This directory contains the core header validation logic for HTTP/1.1, HTTP/2, and HTTP/3:\n\n**Header Validator Core (header_validator.cc/h):**\n- Implements abstract `HeaderValidator` base class with protocol-agnostic validation methods\n- `validateGenericHeaderName()` validates header names against RFC 9110 token definition using character tables to reject invalid characters that could enable injection attacks\n- `validateGenericHeaderValue()` validates header values by checking each character against `kGenericHeaderValueCharTable` to prevent control characters (including CR/LF needed for CRLF injection)\n- `validatePathHeaderCharacters()` validates URI paths to prevent injection\n- `validateContentLengthHeader()` validates Content-Length values as numeric integers\n- `validateHostHeader()` validates Host/Authority headers including detection of deprecated userinfo component (@ character)\n- `validateMethodHeader()` validates HTTP method names\n- `validateSchemeHeader()` validates scheme pseudo-headers (http/https)\n- `sanitizeHeadersWithUnderscores()` drops or rejects headers with underscores based on configuration\n\n**HTTP/1 Validation (http1_header_validator.cc/h):**\n- `ServerHttp1HeaderValidator` and `ClientHttp1HeaderValidator` implement protocol-specific validation\n- `validateRequestHeaders()` validates entire HTTP/1 request header map including Transfer-Encoding and Content-Length\n- `sanitizeContentLength()` handles Content-Length and Transfer-Encoding validation per RFC 9112\n\n**HTTP/2 Validation (http2_header_validator.cc/h):**\n- `ServerHttp2HeaderValidator` and `ClientHttp2HeaderValidator` implement HTTP/2-specific validation\n- Validates pseudo-headers (`:method`, `:path`, `:scheme`, `:authority`)\n- Additional character set validation for path headers that differs from HTTP/1\n\n## Character Validation Tables\n\n**Character Tables (character_tables.h):**\n- `kGenericHeaderValueCharTable`: Allows visible ASCII characters (0x21-0x7E) and extended ASCII (0x80-0xFF), crucially excluding CR (0x0D), LF (0x0A), and NULL (0x00) to prevent CRLF injection\n- `kGenericHeaderNameCharTable`: RFC 9110 token characters (alphanumeric and special chars) for header names\n- `kPathHeaderCharTable`: RFC 3986 compliant characters for URL paths\n- `kMethodHeaderCharTable`: RFC 9110 tchar set for HTTP methods\n\n**Character Set Validation (character_set_validation.h):**\n- `testCharInTable()` utility function uses bit-packed character tables for efficient O(1) character validation\n\n## Internal Header Stripping (Forbidden Headers)\n\n**Connection Manager Utility (conn_manager_utility.cc):**\n- `cleanInternalHeaders()` function removes internal/private headers to prevent downstream exposure and injection:\n  - Edge request headers stripped: `x-envoy-decorator-operation`, `x-envoy-downstream-service-cluster`, `x-envoy-downstream-service-node`, `x-envoy-original-path`\n  - All request headers stripped: `x-envoy-retriable-status-codes`, `x-envoy-retriable-header-names`, `x-envoy-retry-on`, `x-envoy-retry-grpc-on`, `x-envoy-max-retries`, `x-envoy-upstream-alt-stat-name`, `x-envoy-upstream-request-timeout-ms`, `x-envoy-upstream-request-per-try-timeout-ms`, `x-envoy-upstream-request-timeout-alt-response`, `x-envoy-expected-request-timeout-ms`, `x-envoy-force-trace`, `x-envoy-ip-tags`, `x-envoy-original-url`, `x-envoy-hedge-on-per-try-timeout`\n  - Configurable internal-only headers removed via `request_headers.remove(header)` calls\n\n## Header Utility Functions\n\n**Header Utility (header_utility.cc/h):**\n- `headerNameIsValid()`: Validates header names per RFC 7230\n- `headerValueIsValid()`: Validates header values per RFC 7230\n- `headerNameContainsUnderscore()`: Detects headers with underscores for optional rejection\n- `stripTrailingHostDot()`: Removes trailing dots from host headers\n- `stripPortFromHost()`: Removes or validates port in host header\n- `isEnvoyInternalRequest()`: Detects internal Envoy requests\n\n## Path Normalization and Sanitization\n\n**Path Normalizer (path_normalizer.cc/h):**\n- `sanitizePathWithFragment()`: Strips fragments from URL paths to prevent injection\n- `sanitizeEncodedSlashes()`: Handles percent-encoded slash characters per configuration\n- Supports path normalization with configurable behavior for non-compliant characters\n\n## HTTP Codec Implementations\n\n**HTTP/1 Codec (http1/codec_impl.cc):**\n- Handles raw HTTP/1 header parsing with CRLF sequence detection\n- Validates headers during parsing phase before they enter the validation framework\n\n**HTTP/2 Codec (http2/codec_impl.cc):**\n- HTTP/2 uses binary framing, inherently preventing CRLF injection\n- Headers validated by header validator framework after decoding from binary format\n\n## Validation Chain\n\nThe validation flow for incoming HTTP/1 requests:\n1. `conn_manager_impl.cc`: Connection manager receives request\n2. HTTP codec parses raw bytes (http1/codec_impl.cc)\n3. `http1_header_validator.cc::validateRequestHeaders()` performs validation\n4. Character validation via `header_validator.cc::validateGenericHeaderName/Value()` using character tables\n5. Header-specific validation (method, scheme, host, content-length)\n6. `conn_manager_utility.cc::cleanInternalHeaders()` strips forbidden headers\n7. `header_utility.cc` utility functions perform additional sanitization\n\n## Security Properties\n\nThis multi-layered approach prevents header injection attacks by:\n1. **Rejecting CRLF characters**: Character tables explicitly exclude CR/LF preventing raw injection\n2. **Token validation**: Header names must match RFC token definition (alphanumeric plus specific special chars)\n3. **Value validation**: Header values limited to visible ASCII and extended ASCII, excluding control characters\n4. **Forbidden headers**: Internal Envoy headers explicitly stripped before external forwarding\n5. **Underscore handling**: Optional rejection of underscore characters in header names\n6. **Path sanitization**: Fragment stripping and encoded slash handling prevents path-based injection\n7. **Protocol-specific validation**: HTTP/1, HTTP/2, and HTTP/3 validators with protocol-appropriate rules"
}

